FORM.AppraisalAddendumText: -::- -:NEIGHBORHOOD BOUNDARIES:- The immediate neighborhood can be defined as: 400 N. on the north; Ogden Canyon Rd.on the east; 21st Street on the south; Wall Ave. on the west. The market area is the same as the neighborhood and is used for the statistics in the neighborhood section and the 1004MC form. -:NEIGHBORHOOD MARKET CONDITIONS:- Strong price increases took place during the 2004 to 2006 time period but in 2007 and 2008, price increases began to moderate and then fall. In aggregate, home prices in Utah have stabilized since that time. Sales Concessions: Sales prices often include seller concessions, but certainly not in all cases. The amount of those concessions varies, and there is no discernable pattern regarding which properties do, or do not have concessions. Sometimes the concessions appear to increase the price, and sometimes they do not. Because of the erratic nature of seller concessions and their affect on price, it is our conclusion that all concessions need to be subtracted from the final sales price to arrive at a "cash equivalent" price before other adjustments are made. Market Trends: I have considered relevant competitive listings and/or contract offerings in the performance of this appraisal and in the trending information reported in this section. If a trend is indicated, I have attached an addendum providing relevant competitive listing/contract offering data. During the last 6 months, the marketing time has remained stable at about 30 to 60 days. The average list price to sales price ratio is about 97% to 98%. -:COMMENTS ON REBUILDING TO CURRENT DENSITY:- According to Ogden City Planning and Zoning, rebuilding to current density is allowed within one year's time period and subject to Ogden City's approval. -:SINGLE ENTITY OWNS MORE THAN 10% OF UNITS:- The entity of Easy Living, Inc. owns 13 of the 81 units, which equates to 16%. These 13 units are part of phase 2. It is presumed they are rented out. No single entity could provide an exact number of rental units in the project. Kit Garcia (HOA board member) did mention that there were approximately 7% of the units being used as rentals. However, as previously mentioned, Easy Living, Inc. owns 13 units in phase 2. It is presumed these units are being used as rentals. The figure Mr. Garcia provided of 7% rentals is applied to the total number of units in phase 1 and rounded up to 2. -:UNIT CHARGE COMPARISON COMMENTS:- According to the real estate agent, the monthly HOA fee is higher than typical due to a new roof assessment. The fee is temporary and is scheduled to return to the original $145 at a future date. -:COMMENTS ON SALES COMPARISON:- The comparable sales bracket the subject in age, gross living area (GLA) and adjusted sales price. Specific adjustments are made as follows: Comp 1 is located in the subject's project, albeit a different phase. It has fewer bathrooms and is adjusted upward accordingly. It is otherwise quite similar to the subject. Comp 2 is located in a nearby competing complex. It is similar in GLA but has no basement. This comp has an updated kitchen, new carpet and fresh paint and warrants a downward condition adjustment. It also has a central air conditioner and a fireplace, neither of which the subject features. Comp 3 is also located in a nearby competing complex. It has an extra bathroom but has no basement. This comp has a balcony, a covered patio, a fireplace and a central vacuum system. Comp 4 is located in the subject's complex but brackets on the extreme low-end of sales price and adjusted sales price and less weight is therefore place on this sale. Comp 5 was added at the lender's/realtor's request. This comp was not originally used because it is significantly superior than the subject and sold for significantly more than the subject's purchase price. This comp is located in a gated community and a downward adjustment is made based on a paired sales analysis. This comp also has recreational facilities including a clubhouse, swimming pool and tennis courts. A downward adjustment is made based on prior amenity studies. Despite the similar rating, this comp is superior in quality of construction as it has superior exterior ornamentation and appeal. Additionally, this comp has a fully enclosed garage whereas the subject only has a carport. Less weight is placed on this sale due to the large net and gross adjustments. Comp 6 is a current listing in the subject's complex and a downward adjustment is made for the list to sale price ratio as well as median seller concessions. It has no basement but features two carports and a fireplace. The final value is based on Comp 1 as it is located in the subject's project, is the most similar to the subject and has the least amount of adjustments. However, the final value is rounded up to $98,000 due to the upward pull of the other comparable sales. Under the Tidewater Act, the lender was contacted on 12/26/2014 and apprised that the value was coming in below the sales price. The appraiser was provided with several additional comparable sales to consider, one of which was already used in the appraisal report. The additonal comparable sales provided are referenced by the following MLS#'s and a brief explanation as to why they were not used is included: 1222189 (Used as Comp #2) 1210088 (Dated sale) 1219531 (Dated sale) 1239619 (Added as Comp #5) 1186055 (Older sale/significantly larger/gated community) 1220549 (Older sale/significantly larger/gated community)

MARKET.SalesConcessionDescription: The WFRMLS MLS indicates there were 33 closed sales during the past 12 months and 18 of those sales contained seller concessions which is 55% of the total transactions in this market area. Prior Months 7-12: 17 Sales; 8 with concessions; 47% of sales for this period. 4-6: 11 Sales; 5 with concessions; 45% of sales for this period. 0-3: 5 Sales; 5 with concessions; 100% of sales for this period. The concessions ranged between 500 and 5,000. The median concession amount is $2,840.
MARKET.NeighborhoodMarketabilityFactorsDescript: The WFRMLS MLS indicates there were 33 closed sales during the past 12 months and 3 of those sales were either foreclosures or short sales which is 9% of the total transactions in this market area. Prior Months 7-12: 17 Sales; 1 foreclosures or short sales; 6% of sales for this period. 4-6: 11 Sales; 2 foreclosures or short sales; 18% of sales for this period. 0-3: 5 Sales; 0 foreclosures or short sales; 0% of sales for this period.
MARKET.DataSourceDescription: The WFRMLS MLS was the data source used to complete the Market Conditions Addendum.
MARKET.MarketTrendsReconciliationComment: Effective Date: Friday, December 26, 2014 The inventory analysis indicates a mixed market. The number of sales decreased significantly since the previous quarter. The median comparable sale price indicates a drop since the previous quarter but remained stable when compared to the previous year. Little change occurred during the past year for the listing indicator. Most other indicators point to a stable or improving market. This information, together with the appraiser's experience and knowledge, indicates a stable market.

PROPERTY_ANALYSIS._Comment: The improvements have been adequately maintained but do feature typical physical depreciation due to normal wear and tear. With the exception of painted cabinets and walls, no updates have taken place since the owners purchased the subject six years ago. Nevertheless, the home has been adequately maintained over the years.
No adverse site conditions or external factors were noted in the area that would adversely affect the subject property's value.
No additional special features or amenities were noted from the inspection.

_RECONCILIATION._SummaryComment: The value is based on the sales approach. The cost approach is not applicable on condominiums like the subject due to the depreciation factor. The income approach was not used due to lack of data. The scope of the appraisal includes the appraisal process except as noted. The intended client is shown herein but it is understood that others may read the report. The purpose of the appraisal is to estimate the value for a mortgage transaction.
